                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 5.61,
                                "byte_start": 89852,
                                "byte_stop": 112317,
                                "text": "Justice Ginsburg has the opinion of the court in two cases this morning."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 5.61,
                        "stop": 372.715,
                        "byte_start": 112317,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15084,
                            "name": "Ruth Bader Ginsburg",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/ruth_bader_ginsburg",
                            "last_name": "Ginsburg",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2728,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 744958800,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Bill Clinton",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2728"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32681,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 45030,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/ruth_bader_ginsburg_1_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8135,
                            "identifier": "ruth_bader_ginsburg"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 5.61,
                                "stop": 15.65,
                                "byte_start": 112317,
                                "byte_stop": 152546,
                                "text": "The first case that I have to announce is Cunningham against California, No. 05-6551."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.65,
                                "stop": 24.483,
                                "byte_start": 152546,
                                "byte_stop": 187863,
                                "text": "John Cunningham was tried in the California State Court and convicted by a jury of a grade B felony."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 24.483,
                                "stop": 46.878,
                                "byte_start": 187863,
                                "byte_stop": 277411,
                                "text": "Under California\u2019s Determinate Sentencing Law (DSL) Cunningham\u2019s crime was punishable by one of three precise terms of imprisonment, a lower-term sentence of 6 years, a middle-term of 12 years, or an upper-term of 16 years."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 46.878,
                                "stop": 64.185,
                                "byte_start": 277411,
                                "byte_stop": 346688,
                                "text": "The DSL required the trial judge to sentence Cunningham to the 12 year middle-term and nothing more unless the judge found at least one additional fact in aggravation of the event."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 64.185,
                                "stop": 83.824,
                                "byte_start": 346688,
                                "byte_stop": 425160,
                                "text": "The judge found by preponderance of evidence several aggravating facts but only one mitigating fact concluding that the aggravator outweighed the sole mitigator, the judge sentenced Cunningham to the upper term of 16 years."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 83.824,
                                "stop": 88.878,
                                "byte_start": 425160,
                                "byte_stop": 445431,
                                "text": "The California Court of Appeal affirmed the harsher sentence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.878,
                                "stop": 102.197,
                                "byte_start": 445431,
                                "byte_stop": 498721,
                                "text": "We reverse that disposition because the four year sentence alleviation based solely on a judge\u2019s fact finding denied Cunningham his Sixth Amendment right to trial by jury."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.197,
                                "stop": 129.719,
                                "byte_start": 498721,
                                "byte_stop": 608748,
                                "text": "In Apprendi v. New Jersey, we held that under the Sixth Amendment any fact other than a prior conviction that exposes a defendant to a sentence above the otherwise applicable statutory maximum must be found by a jury ,not a judge, for other this sentence elevating facts must be established beyond a reasonable doubt not by a mere preponderance of the evidence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 129.719,
                                "stop": 156.681,
                                "byte_start": 608748,
                                "byte_stop": 716582,
                                "text": "Four years later in Blakely v. Washington we applied the rule stated in Apprendi to the Washington Sentencing Reform Act under that Act the maximum penalty for Blakely\u2019s offense, was 10 years imprisonment but if the trial judge found no facts beyond those reflected in the jury\u2019s verdict Blakely could not receive a sentence above a standard range of 49 to 53 months."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 156.681,
                                "stop": 164.781,
                                "byte_start": 716582,
                                "byte_stop": 749078,
                                "text": "Blakely was sentenced to 90 months imprison based on the judge\u2019s finding of deliberate cruelty."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 164.781,
                                "stop": 172.047,
                                "byte_start": 749078,
                                "byte_stop": 778126,
                                "text": "Applying the rule recognized in Apprendi we held like these sentence unconstitutional."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 172.047,
                                "stop": 181.248,
                                "byte_start": 778126,
                                "byte_stop": 814907,
                                "text": "Last term in United States v. Booker we held the Federal Sentencing Guidelines unconstitutional as a mandatory system."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 181.248,
                                "stop": 189.864,
                                "byte_start": 814907,
                                "byte_stop": 849388,
                                "text": "There was no meaningful distinction we observe between the federal guidelines and the Washington system invalidated in Blakely."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 189.864,
                                "stop": 198.353,
                                "byte_start": 849388,
                                "byte_stop": 883348,
                                "text": "Both systems exposed defendants to greater punishment based solely on facts found by judges not juries."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 198.353,
                                "stop": 211.459,
                                "byte_start": 883348,
                                "byte_stop": 935697,
                                "text": "As a remedy for the Sixth Amendment violation we determine that the federal guideline should remain operative but as advisory only informing but not finding the trial judge."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 211.459,
                                "stop": 221.451,
                                "byte_start": 935697,
                                "byte_stop": 975716,
                                "text": "We also held that sentences imposed under an advisory guidelines regime could be subject to appellate review or reasonableness."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 221.451,
                                "stop": 247.063,
                                "byte_start": 975716,
                                "byte_stop": 1078116,
                                "text": "In all material respect, California\u2019s DSL resembles the sentencing systems invalidated in Blakely and Booker because aggravating facts that authorize the upper-term are found by the judge under California system and maybe established by a preponderance of the evidence and assessment less confining then beyond the reasonable doubt."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 247.063,
                                "stop": 251.527,
                                "byte_start": 1078116,
                                "byte_stop": 1095984,
                                "text": "We hold that the DSL violates the rules stated in Apprendi."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 251.527,
                                "stop": 271.147,
                                "byte_start": 1095984,
                                "byte_stop": 1174456,
                                "text": "In People v. Black, the California Supreme Court attempted to rescue the DSL\u2019s judicial factfinding authorization by describing the system as imposing only a reasonableness constraint equivalent to the constraint operative in the federal system for Booker."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 271.147,
                                "stop": 286.502,
                                "byte_start": 1174456,
                                "byte_stop": 1235896,
                                "text": "The reasonableness check the Booker court anticipated however would operates within constitutional constraints delineated in this Court\u2019s precedent and not as a substitute for those constraints."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 286.502,
                                "stop": 298.003,
                                "byte_start": 1235896,
                                "byte_stop": 1281872,
                                "text": "Because the DSL allocates to judges sole authority to find facts on which the imposition of an upper term sentence turns the system violates the Sixth Amendment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 298.003,
                                "stop": 308.566,
                                "byte_start": 1281872,
                                "byte_stop": 1324190,
                                "text": "The remedy prescribed in Booker, in short, is not properly regarded as a recipe for rendering this Court\u2019s Sixth Amendment case law toothless."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 308.566,
                                "stop": 315.91,
                                "byte_start": 1324190,
                                "byte_stop": 1353552,
                                "text": "As to the adjustment of California sentencing system in light of our ruling the ball lies in California\u2019s court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 315.91,
                                "stop": 332.374,
                                "byte_start": 1353552,
                                "byte_stop": 1419380,
                                "text": "Several States have modified their systems in the wake of Apprendi and Blakely to retain determinate sentencing, by calling upon the jury to find any fact necessary to the imposition of an elevated sentence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 332.374,
                                "stop": 346.899,
                                "byte_start": 1419380,
                                "byte_stop": 1477476,
                                "text": "Other States have chosen to permit judges genuinely \u201cto exercise broad discretion within a statutory range\u201d, for example a range running from 6-16 years without a mandatory middle."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 346.899,
                                "stop": 360.132,
                                "byte_start": 1477476,
                                "byte_stop": 1530453,
                                "text": "California may follow the path taken by its sister States or otherwise alter its system, so long as it observes Sixth Amendment limitations declared in this Court\u2019s decisions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 360.132,
                                "stop": 372.715,
                                "byte_start": 1530453,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Kennedy has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justice Breyer joins, Justice Alito has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justices Kennedy and Breyer join."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
